Prerequisites

AWS CLI Configured: Ensure your shell environment has valid AWS credentials configured (aws configure or environment variables)
with permissions for ec2:DescribeInstances.

SSH Authorization: The public key corresponding to your private key must be listed in the target instances' ~/.ssh/authorized_keys file.

Step 1: Grant Execution Permissions

chmod +x cloud_fleet_stats.sh

Trigger Fleet Discovery Sweep
Run the script by passing the path to your AWS SSH identity key:

./cloud_fleet_stats.sh ~/.ssh/my-aws-key.pem

Step 3: Inspect Consolidated Telemetry
Inspect the timestamped output log generated by the execution sweep:

cat cloud_fleet_telemetry_*.log

